release.notes:
From the Acoustic Sounds website:
Mastered by Ryan K. Smith at Sterling Sound from the original analog tapes.
180-gram LPs pressed at Quality Record Pressings.
Stoughton Printing gatefold old-style tip-on jackets.
Series supervised by Chad Kassem CEO of Acoustic Sounds.

Issued with an Acoustic Sound Series 'Releases beginning in 2020' color insert and vinyl housed in a non-labelled rice paper inner sleeve

From back of sleeve:
Printed in U.S.A.
A Verve Records release. Originally released in 1962 on Impulse! Records
© 2021 UMG Recordings, Inc., 1755 Broadway New York, NY 10019 - U.S.A. Distributed by Universal Music Enterprises, A Division of UMG Recordings, Inc.

From labels:
Printed in U.S.A. A Verve Records release. Originally released in 1962 on Impulse! Records © 2021 UMG Recordings, Inc.

From inside of sleeve:
Recorded at The Village Vanguard, NYC, November 2 and 3, 1961

From Acoustic Sounds Series sticker:
• Mastered from the original analog tapes by top mastering engineers
• Manufactured at Quality Record Pressings (QRP) on 180 gram vinyl
• Gatefold sleeves printed at Stoughton Printing Company

Catalogue numbers:
- A-10-S on labels
- A-10 on sleeve

Runouts:
Etched except 'STERLING' is stamped both sides
